        {
          "id": "c8f42aa1-b955-4892-b93b-897a09454e1f",
          "type": "h1",
          "content": "Intro to Algorithms"
        },
        {
          "id": "8af85f3c-7c2f-42fd-af73-51db60011ee1",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": "This master document is maintained by the community. Fork it to your personal workspace, add your own notes, and contribute back through the merge pipeline."
        },
        {
          "id": "9fe8df36-942e-43e0-9c04-f607a775018c",
          "type": "h2",
          "content": "The Chain Rule"
        },
        {
          "id": "e2168c8c-b00f-45b5-9388-a5cd5d076a13",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": "Let $f$ and $g$ be differentiable functions. Then the composite function $f \\circ g$ is differentiable, and"
        },
        {
          "id": "0583ff9a-a689-43f2-b123-14796a6f55da",
          "type": "latex",
          "content": "\\frac{d}{dx}\\bigl[f\\bigl(g(x)\\bigr)\\bigr] = f'\\bigl(g(x)\\bigr) \\cdot g'(x)"
        },
        {
          "id": "dfe955c0-7236-4ce0-8a27-3d18a1cc0d70",
          "type": "h3",
          "content": "Worked Example"
        },
        {
          "id": "f3222abb-8b3b-42c8-b24d-123221489cb7",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": "Find $\\frac{d}{dx}[\\sin(x^2)]$. Let $f(u) = \\sin(u)$ and $g(x) = x^2$. Then:"
        },
        {
          "id": "07b474e9-8936-4f88-8321-c6f4fa857228",
          "type": "latex",
          "content": "\\frac{d}{dx}\\bigl[\\sin(x^2)\\bigr] = \\cos(x^2) \\cdot 2x"
        },
        {
          "id": "790156fd-a96b-4b82-a6a9-d1019d643590",
          "type": "h2",
          "content": "Binary Search"
        },
        {
          "id": "4cefd1bc-2fc3-4c47-8e4d-a1a306c6f3fd",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": "A classic $O(\\log n)$ search algorithm on a sorted array. Repeatedly halves the search interval."
        },
        {
          "id": "ada2ca85-36c0-48cd-86e9-f81dde3bb036",
          "type": "code",
          "content": "def binary_search(arr, target):\n    \"\"\"Search for target in sorted array.\n\n    Time:  O(log n)\n    Space: O(1)\n    \"\"\"\n    low, high = 0, len(arr) - 1\n\n    while low <= high:\n        mid = (low + high) // 2\n        if arr[mid] == target:\n            return mid\n        elif arr[mid] < target:\n            low = mid + 1\n        else:\n            high = mid - 1\n\n    return -1  # not found",
          "meta": {
            "language": "python",
            "filename": "binary_search.py"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "a8ab4c31-1ea6-461d-8991-603f5bdf0882",
          "type": "h3",
          "content": "Complexity Comparison"
        },
        {
          "id": "ee7c7435-e338-40aa-99d5-5017276a5547",
          "type": "table",
          "content": "Algorithm,Best,Average,Worst,Space\nLinear Search,O(1),O(n),O(n),O(1)\nBinary Search,O(1),O(log n),O(log n),O(1)\nHash Table,O(1),O(1),O(n),O(n)",
          "meta": {
            "caption": "Table 1. Search algorithm complexities"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "6f24fd66-8bb8-42ed-ad26-1b69fcaeff01",
          "type": "divider",
          "content": ""
        },
        {
          "id": "5d8f49e1-f362-47c3-a09c-7867310d0d94",
          "type": "h2",
          "content": "Chemistry Cross-Domain"
        },
        {
          "id": "21203fa3-5cf8-4fc5-8059-fb79b90ef83d",
          "type": "chemistry",
          "content": "\\text{N}_2 + 3\\text{H}_2 \\rightleftharpoons 2\\text{NH}_3 \\quad (\\Delta H = -92.4\\;\\text{kJ/mol})",
          "meta": {
            "caption": "Haber Process"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
