          }
        },
        {
          "id": "96a4a250-c76b-4f94-bd66-57919c4e6c4d",
          "type": "h2",
          "content": "The Chain Rule"
        },
        {
          "id": "6d4c1c5b-3679-46de-a296-717ad611b2f9",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": "The chain rule is all about composites — \"outside-inside.\" Apply the outer derivative first, then multiply by the inner derivative."
        },
        {
          "id": "c07a2c3f-78d4-44f2-a73a-41b8886169c8",
          "type": "latex",
          "content": "\\frac{d}{dx}\\bigl[f\\bigl(g(x)\\bigr)\\bigr] = f'\\bigl(g(x)\\bigr) \\cdot g(x)",
          "meta": {}
        },
        {
          "id": "f06c6648-ee57-4614-958c-6b2d7e73686c",
          "type": "h3",
          "content": "My Example Walkthrough"
        },
        {
          "id": "ddfb6ec0-71c8-40e9-9904-a17e73111209",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": "Differentiate $\\sin(x^2)$: outer is $\\sin$, inner is $x^2$."
        },
        {
          "id": "de3fbf4d-6c4f-49c9-87b7-fa9874169b62",
          "type": "latex",
          "content": "\\frac{d}{dx}\\bigl[\\sin(x^2)\\bigr] = \\cos(x^2) \\cdot 2x",
          "meta": {}
        },
        {
          "id": "b8537906-1cbe-45f3-80dd-f04b3e4b3448",
          "type": "callout",
          "content": "Key insight: we get cos(x²) — outer deriv evaluated AT the inner function — times 2x — the inner deriv. This pattern repeats for every chain rule problem.",
          "meta": {
            "calloutType": "tip"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "be9edf6c-fd41-4223-b9c6-a64e0e6f7646",
          "type": "h2",
          "content": "Binary Search Notes hello there"
        },
        {
          "id": "c0181e68-7eab-4626-8332-0ebb1f2d8ebd",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": "Binary search only works on **sorted** arrays. The invariant is: target is always in [low, high] if it exists."
        },
        {
          "id": "65d427fe-70d8-48df-af4e-e456e074314e",
          "type": "code",
          "content": "def binary_search(arr, target):\n    low, high = 0, len(arr) - 1\n    while low <= high:\n        mid = (low + high) // 2\n        if arr[mid] == target:\n            return mid\n        elif arr[mid] < target:\n            low = mid + 1\n        else:\n            high = mid - 1\n    return -1",
          "meta": {
            "language": "python",
            "filename": "binary_search.py"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "caccb7dd-3774-4574-b899-dbe7e4de3521",
          "type": "latex",
          "content": "x = \\frac{-b \\pm \\sqrt{b^2 - 4ac}}{2a}",
          "meta": {}
        },
        {
