      "blocks": [
        {
          "id": "58d76b5d-f828-4ee6-aa87-ffa406115292",
          "type": "h1",
          "content": "Linear Algebra"
        },
        {
          "id": "61aaf7ac-8423-41e0-8f92-031ede62e05c",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": "Linear algebra is the branch of mathematics that studies vector spaces and linear mappings between them."
        },
        {
          "id": "b90dbee8-ab90-43f3-8272-48e4be81c8f8",
          "type": "h2",
          "content": "Matrix Multiplication"
        },
        {
          "id": "c9897507-3015-4596-a2b5-171c3332d664",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": "For matrices $A \\in \\mathbb{R}^{m \\times k}$ and $B \\in \\mathbb{R}^{k \\times n}$, the product $C = AB \\in \\mathbb{R}^{m \\times n}$ is:"
        },
        {
          "id": "205bc56f-db25-439e-b26a-ae6d3ad7907f",
          "type": "latex",
          "content": "C_{ij} = \\sum_{r=1}^{k} A_{ir} B_{rj}"
        },
        {
          "id": "b3f3c40f-0bfa-4f96-bfb7-5267f8a72585",
          "type": "h2",
          "content": "Eigenvalues & Eigenvectors"
        },
        {
          "id": "273d8f1e-062c-4181-80c8-94d96c2365ed",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": "A scalar $\\lambda$ is an eigenvalue of matrix $A$ if there exists a nonzero vector $\\mathbf{v}$ (the eigenvector) such that:"
        },
        {
          "id": "19b8fff3-1a2f-4a46-808f-b91c010f452f",
          "type": "latex",
          "content": "A\\mathbf{v} = \\lambda \\mathbf{v}"
        },
        {
          "id": "87b041e2-fc50-47cc-85e3-0cce54ad9c2f",
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": "Eigenvalues are found by solving the characteristic equation:"
        },
        {
          "id": "8d51bf93-dc8b-4db1-8e65-588d6dfc5484",
          "type": "latex",
          "content": "\\det(A - \\lambda I) = 0"
        }
      ]
    }
  }
